com.bluegosling.reflect

Interface EnumType.EnumElement<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of an element's value
    All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<EnumType.EnumElement<T>>, Supplier<T>
    Enclosing class:
    EnumType<T>

    public static interface EnumType.EnumElement<T>
extends Supplier<T>, Comparable<EnumType.EnumElement<T>>
    Represents a single element in an enumeration. This is a wrapper around a single enum value and provides accessor methods for the element's name and ordinal position.

      • compareTo

        default int compareTo(EnumType.EnumElement<T> o)
        Compares this element to another. The two elements are not comparable if they belong to different enum types, and an IllegalArgumentException is thrown in this case. Otherwise, the ordering of elements is based on their ordinal position, so an element with a lower ordinal position is "less than" an element with a higher one.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface Comparable<EnumType.EnumElement<T>>

        Throws:
